1
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:17,600
Please keep my daughter away
from harm.

2
00:00:17,667 --> 00:00:22,033
Don't let her cross paths
with Rina.

3
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,767
I don't want my daughter
to get hurt

4
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:26,567
and involved in Rina's wrath.

5
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:28,300
I'm only human.

6
00:00:28,367 --> 00:00:33,733
If Rina hurts my daughter,
I will never back down.

7
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:34,400
Call her.

8
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:35,800
She doesn't have a phone.

9
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:37,667
Red, everyone has a cell phone.

10
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,367
I don't know, Mom.

11
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:40,767
I'm confused too.

12
00:00:40,833 --> 00:00:45,433
His family is the reason
my mom went to jail.

13
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,633
I also couldn't accept it
if I were in your shoes.

14
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:50,667
If acceptance is easy,

15
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:53,533
then everyone can move on
that easily.

16
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,200
They met at the campus.

17
00:00:55,267 --> 00:00:57,400
I went there to meet her,
and then she disappeared.

18
00:00:57,467 --> 00:00:59,467
She targeted Red.

19
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:01,133
Because she knows
he's from an affluent family.

20
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,633
So Yenyen is some kind
of a gold digger?

21
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:08,100
I think it's better
if you meet her.

22
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:10,567
So you can see for yourself.

23
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:12,000
How is he?

24
00:01:12,067 --> 00:01:13,533
When are you going
to introduce him to me?

25
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:17,533
If I love him, I'll have
to love his family too.

26
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,567
But I can't do that.

27
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:22,267
So it will be better
if I stay away from him.

28
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:26,000
I haven't been getting any sleep
from thinking about her.

29
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:29,433
I hope she'll find the courage
to tell me

30
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,333
what she really feels.

31
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:59,200
Coach, I'm sorry.

32
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:01,533
I don't know what to do about
my situation with Red.

33
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:04,667
If only you were here.

34
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:09,333
Maybe I can ask you
for some advice.

35
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,200
I'm so confused.

36
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:15,467
My heart says that I love Red.

37
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:18,600
But my mind says otherwise.

38
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:21,033
Because of what his family
did to my mom.

39
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:24,267
Which one should I listen to?

40
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:51,600
Yen, what's wrong?

41
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:54,800
Why did you disappear
all of a sudden?

42
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:57,067
You didn't even say a word.

43
00:02:57,133 --> 00:02:58,200
You didn't talk to me.

44
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,400
Red, sorry.

45
00:03:02,467 --> 00:03:04,100
I have to do something.

46
00:03:04,167 --> 00:03:05,967
Excuse me.

47
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,067
Yen!

48
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:07,700
Wait!

49
00:03:09,267 --> 00:03:10,667
Please talk to me.

50
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:12,100
What did I do wrong?

51
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:16,467
Did I do anything wrong?

52
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:17,733
What is it? Don't make it hard
for me.

53
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,600
Tell me.

54
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:21,500
Forget I exist.

55
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,500
This will be the last time
you'll see me.

56
00:03:25,567 --> 00:03:28,467
From now on, never speak
to me again.

57
00:03:29,833 --> 00:03:30,600
Yen!

58
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,700
Rice cakes!

59
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:41,733
My rice cakes are good!

60
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,000
- It's almost gone.
- Can I buy some?

61
00:03:44,067 --> 00:03:45,133
Oh!

62
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,233
Thank you.

63
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,267
Thank you.

64
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:52,467
Rice cakes!

65
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,600
Rice cakes!

66
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:07,367
Yen, hold on!

67
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:11,033
Can you please talk to me?

68
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:12,200
I'm begging you!

69
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,400
Why are you being like this?

70
00:04:14,467 --> 00:04:17,500
Red, there's nothing left for us
to talk about.

71
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:20,000
Didn't I tell you that this will
be the last time you'll see me?

72
00:04:20,067 --> 00:04:21,200
It's over.

73
00:04:24,067 --> 00:04:24,867
Why?
Are you giving up on us
just like that?

74
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:32,400
Are you breaking up with me
all of a sudden?

75
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:38,433
Didn't we promise each other
we'd never part?

76
00:04:41,267 --> 00:04:43,067
Red, we're not meant
for each other.

77
00:04:46,367 --> 00:04:49,100
So, please, stop talking to me.

78
00:04:50,467 --> 00:04:51,433
It's over.

79
00:04:52,467 --> 00:04:54,233
This is for the better.

80
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:56,067
No, Yen.

81
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:57,233
I can't let you do this.

82
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:01,333
We're both in this relationship.

83
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:03,067
So we both have a say.

84
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:05,500
Don't be unfair!

85
00:05:07,267 --> 00:05:08,233
Unfair?

86
00:05:10,567 --> 00:05:14,067
You can say whatever you want.

87
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:14,967
Yes, it's unfair.

88
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:19,700
The same way your family's
been unfair to my mom.

89
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:21,167
What?

90
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:22,133
What do you mean?

91
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,667
Don't try to follow me, Red.

92
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:24,667
Just leave me alone.

93
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:26,267
Yen!

94
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,400
What are you talking about?

95
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:32,400
Why did you say that my family's
been unfair to your mom?

96
00:05:32,467 --> 00:05:34,067
They haven't even met yet.

97
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:00,933
How did it go?

98
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,533
Just as you asked.

99
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,667
I robbed that woman.

100
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:08,333
Okay, consider your debt
paid off.

101
00:06:08,433 --> 00:06:09,433
Thank you.

102
00:06:13,033 --> 00:06:14,633
You're that man! You bastard!

103
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:16,633
Bastard!

104
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:24,400
I know you.

105
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,467
You were supposed to meet
my mom, right?

106
00:06:43,567 --> 00:06:45,067
She was so excited to meet you.

107
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:46,233
But you left all of a sudden.

108
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:51,067
Yen, why are you being
like this?

109
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:56,033
Why are you giving up on us?

110
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:57,367
Don't do this to me!

111
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:00,467
I'm not a fortune teller.

112
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,133
I can't figure out
what's in your head.

113
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,167
You have to tell me. Talk to me!

114
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:11,033
Look, you're still wearing
the bracelet I gave you.

115
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:13,000
It means you still care for us,
Yen.

116
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,033
Don't waste our relationship.
You're wasting what we have.

117
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:21,533
Sorry, Red.

118
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,300
There's no more us.

119
00:07:27,467 --> 00:07:29,233
It's over.

120
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:11,033
What?

121
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,700
You broke up with him!

122
00:08:12,767 --> 00:08:14,267
Tell me all about it!

123
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:15,133
Let's go over there. Hurry!

124
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:18,367
Did you break up with him?

125
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:19,600
Are you sure that's
what you want?

126
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:22,700
I have no choice but to do it.

127
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:26,500
That's how our relationship
will end anyway.

128
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:31,233
I will do anything
for my mom's sake.

129
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:34,467
My mom suffered many years
in jail.

130
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:39,233
We've been separated
for a long time.

131
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:42,333
She lost her chance
to be a mother.

132
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:46,000
And all of that happened
because of Red's family.

133
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:53,667
Eden, it must be hard
to forget about him.

134
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:54,700
Can you bear it?

135
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,667
I have no choice.

136
00:08:57,667 --> 00:09:01,133
It will be difficult,
but I have to do it.

137
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:06,400
You know that it's my first time
falling in love.

138
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:08,167
It's also my first heartache.

139
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,667
I experienced all my firsts
from Red.

140
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,367
First heartache...

141
00:09:16,433 --> 00:09:18,167
that hurts.

142
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:22,467
I don't need to tell you this,

143
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:24,467
but I'm here whenever you need
someone to talk to,

144
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:26,000
someone who cares,
I'll be anything you need.

145
00:09:26,067 --> 00:09:28,333
I can be your enemy
if you need me to.

146
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:30,700
No need for that. I'm okay.

147
00:09:30,767 --> 00:09:33,467
I have my mom.

148
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:36,200
I'll focus on her.

149
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:38,233
I'll spend all my time with her.

150
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:43,200
I'm happy with my decision.

151
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,133
You're happy.

152
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:48,233
Let me see how happy you are.

153
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:51,500
Oh, I believe you!

154
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,633
I'm so happy for you, Eden.

155
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:54,533
You look so happy.

156
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,033
Crazy!

157
00:10:04,733 --> 00:10:08,100
Amanda, are you sure?

158
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:10,133
Do you know who's behind the man
who robbed you?

159
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:16,500
I've seen him before.

160
00:10:16,567 --> 00:10:20,000
That was at Rina's house when
I was still working there.

161
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,233
You have a pretty maid, Sis.

162
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:47,400
Zandro, can you knock it off?

163
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:49,200
If you want coffee,
then you better drink it now.

164
00:10:49,267 --> 00:10:51,133
Victor might see you here.

165
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,700
He's Rina's brother!

166
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:15,067
So that means Rina's behind all
of this to take revenge on you!

167
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:19,033
I'm sure she made him do it!

168
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,633
I can't let this slide anymore!

169
00:11:20,700 --> 00:11:23,167
What if they try to hurt Yenyen?

170
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:26,667
I will let her know
that I'm not afraid of her!

171
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:28,700
Amanda, calm down, please.

172
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:31,467
How can we prove
that they're behind it?

173
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:33,733
Are we going to file a case
against Rina?

174
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,333
Are we going to file
a complaint?

175
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,433
- What are we going to do?
- No!

176
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:39,133
I will make her pay myself!

177
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,067
I will give her
what she deserves!

178
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,000
Amanda! Wait,
where are you going?
- No! Stay here!
- I'm coming with you.

179
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,400
- No, you're not! Stay there!
- Amanda!

180
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:48,067
- Amanda!
- Stay there!

181
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:49,000
Fine!

182
00:11:57,733 --> 00:11:59,733
Red...

183
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,033
you're not eating your food.

184
00:12:02,667 --> 00:12:04,600
Don't you like it?

185
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:06,167
What would you like to eat?

186
00:12:06,233 --> 00:12:07,700
I'll cook it for you.
What would you like?

187
00:12:09,067 --> 00:12:10,567
I don't feel like eating, Mom.

188
00:12:13,033 --> 00:12:14,600
Is it because of Yenyen?

189
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,467
She doesn't want
to see me anymore.

190
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:23,633
Why? What's the problem?

191
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:27,000
I have no idea, Mom.

192
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:29,533
All she said was that
we're not meant for each other.

193
00:12:31,067 --> 00:12:33,367
I'm just so confused right now.

194
00:12:33,433 --> 00:12:35,033
Look, if she doesn't want to be
with you, then let her be.

195
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,433
Right?

196
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:38,000
Don't force her.

197
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:39,400
It's not right

198
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:42,600
to be with someone who felt
half-hearted about you.

199
00:12:42,667 --> 00:12:43,633
And besides...

200
00:12:44,667 --> 00:12:46,767
Sabina's there for you.

201
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:50,333
I believe she's the best one
for you.

202
00:12:50,433 --> 00:12:52,167
But I love Yenyen.

203
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:54,400
But she doesn't want you!

204
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:56,067
Come on, Red.

205
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:57,700
There are a lot of women
out there.

206
00:12:57,767 --> 00:12:59,967
Yenyen is just one of them.

207
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,367
What about our promises
that we will never part ways?

208
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:05,100
That we won't give up
on each other?

209
00:13:05,167 --> 00:13:07,233
That we'll stay together
forever?

210
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,533
- Sir.
- Yes?

211
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:14,467
Can you call your employer?

212
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:15,633
They're not home.

213
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:16,200
- They're not home?
- Yes, Ma'am.

214
00:13:16,267 --> 00:13:17,333
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

215
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,167
Rina!

216
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:19,433
Ma'am, please don't make
a scene here.

217
00:13:22,433 --> 00:13:23,300
Oh my God!

218
00:13:25,433 --> 00:13:26,400
Wait.

219
00:13:27,833 --> 00:13:30,067
Yen! I'm glad you're now here!

220
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:33,000
- Your mom!
- Why? What happened?

221
00:13:33,067 --> 00:13:35,400
Rina did something awful
to your mom again!

222
00:13:35,467 --> 00:13:36,667
Ma'am Rina?

223
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:39,500
What did she do?
Did she hurt my mom?

224
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:43,100
She had her robbed!
They took all her money!

225
00:13:43,167 --> 00:13:46,467
How did my mom find out
that Rina was behind it?

226
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:49,467
Because your mom recognized
the guy who paid the robber.

227
00:13:49,533 --> 00:13:50,400
It's Rina's brother.

228
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:53,533
That's why your mom went
to their house now!

229
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,367
- Auntie!
- We have to follow her!

230
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:58,167
- Let's go, Auntie!
- She can't go to jail again.

231
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:00,600
- My God!
- She can't go to jail again!

232
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:01,967
I can't be separated
from her again!

233
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:03,433
Auntie, let's go!

234
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:06,367
Ma'am, someone's looking
for you outside.

235
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:07,067
Who is it?

236
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:08,167
She said her name was Amanda.

237
00:14:09,767 --> 00:14:13,533
She has the guts to come here!

238
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,167
What does she want?

239
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:16,333
Who's Amanda?

240
00:14:17,733 --> 00:14:20,200
She's the woman who killed
your older brother!

241
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,300
Mom.

242
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:46,533
- Rina!
- Ma'am, it's already late.

243
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,033
Please don't make a scene here.

244
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:49,000
I don't care about the time!

245
00:14:49,067 --> 00:14:51,033
- Please Ma'am.
- Rina, come out of there!

246
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,200
Ma'am, please don't make
a scene here.

247
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,300
It's already late at night.

248
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:55,567
- Rina!
- Ma'am, please.

249
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:57,167
Don't make a scene here!

250
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:58,333
Get your employer.

251
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,167
She's not here.

252
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:00,567
So who's behind you?

253
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:01,533
- Who's that?
- Guard!

254
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:03,400
- Mom!
- Open the gate!

255
00:15:03,467 --> 00:15:04,233
- Okay.
- Mom!

256
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:08,933
What do you want?

257
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:10,933
I'm here to collect your debt.

258
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:16,467
You really have the guts
to show up here?

259
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:19,067
Your gut is unbelievable!

260
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:20,700
It's galvanized!

261
00:15:20,767 --> 00:15:22,367
We don't owe you anything!

262
00:15:22,433 --> 00:15:24,367
Yes, you do! You owe me a lot!

263
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:28,167
And I know that
you're using Zandro

264
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,600
to make my life miserable!

265
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:31,167
Let me see your brother!

266
00:15:31,233 --> 00:15:33,167
- Zandro won't be facing you.
- Oh, really?

267
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:48,367
Mom!

268
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:51,133
- No!
- Now, tell me.

269
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,467
Where do you want your head
to drop?

270
00:15:53,533 --> 00:15:55,133
To your right?

271
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,033
Or left?

272
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:03,233
Answer me!

273
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,233
Mom!

274
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:05,700
Do you want your head
to drop to the ground?

275
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:09,100
- Mom, give that to me!
- Can you do it?

276
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,200
Give it to me. You might end up
hurting her, Mom.

277
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:12,400
What's going on here?

278
00:16:12,467 --> 00:16:15,367
This woman has the guts
to show up here!

279
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:17,700
And now she's accusing me
of all kinds of things!

280
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:22,533
I'm not just accusing you!
I'm telling the truth, Rina!

281
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,367
Excuse me.

282
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:26,133
But you have to leave.

283
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:29,200
We're all civilized people here.

284
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,167
Please leave.

285
00:16:33,233 --> 00:16:38,100
I'm not going anywhere until
I see your brother Zandro.

286
00:16:38,167 --> 00:16:41,133
Why? What do you want
to tell him?

287
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:44,433
We don't have time to talk
to a criminal like you.

288
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:48,767
Criminals are not welcome
in my home!

289
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:51,633
So you don't belong
in your home!

290
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:53,033
Because you're a criminal!

291
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:54,033
What a pest!

292
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:59,700
I know you told your crook
brother to rob me!

293
00:16:59,767 --> 00:17:01,667
You don't have the right
to talk to my mom like that!

294
00:17:01,733 --> 00:17:04,333
- Oh, really?
- Get out of here!

295
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,267
You don't want to leave?

296
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,100
No? Give me that!

297
00:17:07,167 --> 00:17:08,233
Mom! No!

298
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,500
- You'll hurt her!
- Give it to me!

299
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:10,567
No!

300
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:11,600
Fine!

301
00:17:11,667 --> 00:17:13,433
Mom! What are you going to do?

302
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,033
- Mom! Stop!
- You!

303
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:16,033
You're like...

304
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,733
You're like the ground
we walk on and spit on!

305
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,100
Mom! My God!

306
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:28,000
That's what you deserve!

307
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:29,200
I'll give you what you deserve!

308
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:32,133
No!

309
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,367
What is she doing?

310
00:17:35,433 --> 00:17:36,233
- Oh my God!
- What is she doing?
- This...
- Ma'am...

311
00:17:37,267 --> 00:17:40,500
- Don't do it!
- This is what you deserve!

312
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:41,633
Oh my God!

313
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:56,667
Auntie, let's hurry!
My mom could be in trouble!

314
00:17:56,733 --> 00:18:01,067
I wish my sister didn't
cross paths with Rina.

315
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:04,300
I wish she never worked
for them.

316
00:18:04,367 --> 00:18:08,433
I don't know why our family
has to cross paths with theirs!

317
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:10,067
I also don't know why, Auntie.

318
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:13,300
But destiny made me cross paths
with her son too!

319
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,333
Wait, hold on.

320
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,033
What do you mean by that?

321
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:22,633
Auntie...

322
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:29,133
the guy I was
with on the island...

323
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,167
What?

324
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:32,133
He is Rina's son.

325
00:18:40,133 --> 00:18:41,967
OMG!

326
00:18:42,033 --> 00:18:45,000
We became close.

327
00:18:45,067 --> 00:18:47,600
We fell in love with each other.

328
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:50,300
Wait, wait a minute!
I can't absorb all of this!

329
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:52,300
- Did your mom know about this?
- No, Auntie!

330
00:18:52,367 --> 00:18:54,733
My mom can't find out
about this!

331
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,067
But don't worry.

332
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,033
I'm staying away from him.

333
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:05,300
I chose my mom more than him.

334
00:19:07,267 --> 00:19:08,600
- Let's go look for your mom.
- Auntie...

335
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:11,000
My God! What a headache!

336
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,967
My God!

337
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:15,267
You're so gross, Amanda!

338
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:18,200
- You're a pig! Pig!
- Your attitude is gross!

339
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:19,667
Dog shit is nothing
compared to you!

340
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,100
That's enough!

341
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:22,533
Stop it!

342
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:25,467
No one can disrespect my mom!

343
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:26,967
Haven't you had enough?

344
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:29,567
You hurt our family
when you killed my brother!

345
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:30,700
What else do you want?

346
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,233
Get out of here before
I call the cops on you!

347
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:36,567
You can't scare me!

348
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:40,667
I lived with cops for 8 years
because of what your mom did!

349
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:42,567
Go on. Drag her away from here!

350
00:19:42,633 --> 00:19:44,133
- Get out of here!
- Leave!

351
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:46,300
Get out of here, Amanda!

352
00:19:46,367 --> 00:19:47,667
Just leave!

353
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:48,700
Mom, let's go.

354
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,400
Does it smell good?

355
00:19:52,467 --> 00:19:53,433
Does it smell like you?

356
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:54,633
Gross!

357
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:55,567
She's gross!

358
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:01,067
- Mom!
- Amanda!

359
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:03,000
Mom, what happened to you?

360
00:20:03,100 --> 00:20:05,533
Rina's son is just like her!

361
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,400
They're both monsters!

362
00:20:10,267 --> 00:20:11,733
My God! I'm so dirty!

363
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,733
Look at me! So gross!

364
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,033
Gross!

365
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:15,300
My God!

366
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:16,167
I need to wash!

367
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:18,033
Wait, I'm going to wash.

368
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:19,067
Do you have a towel?

369
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:21,133
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Okay.

370
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,600
I just going to wash my hands.

371
00:20:24,267 --> 00:20:26,000
God!

372
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:27,033
Tissue.

373
00:20:28,433 --> 00:20:30,400
Alcohol. Wait, wait!

374
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:33,600
Okay. Alcohol.

375
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:34,500
And can you fix...

376
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:35,600
That's enough!

377
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:37,267
I said enough.
Can you fix my bath?

378
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,133
- Okay, Ma'am.
- Thank you.

379
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,167
God!

380
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,433
I'm glad you're here.

381
00:20:45,233 --> 00:20:47,600
Someone will protect me
from Amanda.

382
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:51,433
Of course, Mom!
I won't let her harm you.

383
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,467
But next time, Mom,
don't use this samurai.

384
00:20:53,533 --> 00:20:55,500
You might hurt someone.

385
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:56,733
Oh, well!

386
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,367
I don't care!

387
00:20:58,433 --> 00:21:00,333
Did you see that woman?
The nerve!

388
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,433
She came to our house for what?

389
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,200
To cause trouble?
She'll cause us trouble?

390
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:07,667
Honestly, what's wrong
with that woman?

391
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:09,400
She won't leave us alone!

392
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:11,567
I hate her!

393
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,533
I hate her too, Mom.

394
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:19,700
When I was a kid, I didn't know
any better.

395
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:22,200
I didn't understand
what was going on.

396
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:25,033
But everything is clear
to me now.

397
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:26,300
It's all her fault.

398
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:28,000
She's so evil.

399
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:29,967
All the suffering, the grief.

400
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:33,133
I know, Son. And you saw her,
right?

401
00:21:34,467 --> 00:21:37,067
She had the nerve to come here!

402
00:21:39,767 --> 00:21:41,467
Mom...

403
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:43,300
don't worry.

404
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,700
I will protect you, okay?

405
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:47,000
I will protect you and dad.

406
00:21:48,633 --> 00:21:52,033
If she tries anything again,
she'll have to face me!

407
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:53,233
And her whole family too.

408
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:58,700
You shouldn't have come here
alone.

409
00:21:58,767 --> 00:22:00,567
You know what her family's
capable of, right?

410
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:02,167
Yes, you're right.

411
00:22:02,233 --> 00:22:04,067
Her son thinks I'm the bad guy!

412
00:22:04,133 --> 00:22:07,467
He's so convinced that his mom
is so innocent and kind!

413
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:08,967
He doesn't know that
his mom is a demon!

414
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,233
Amanda, let's just go home.

415
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:18,433
And let's just stay away
from them, please.

416
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,600
Please, Amanda.

417
00:22:19,667 --> 00:22:20,433
Yes, you're right.

418
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:21,633
We'll go away

419
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:25,633
because we'll never have peace
if they know where we are.

420
00:22:28,133 --> 00:22:29,467
- Let's go, Mom.
- Come on.

421
00:22:29,533 --> 00:22:31,067
- Let's go.
- Amanda...

422
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,067
Are you okay?

423
00:22:57,133 --> 00:23:00,200
What is that criminal
doing here?

424
00:23:00,267 --> 00:23:01,633
Eden!

425
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,167
- Mom!
- You forgot your lunch.

426
00:23:04,233 --> 00:23:05,700
Thank you, Mom.

427
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:08,067
I'll do anything
for my daughter.

428
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:11,067
You know how much I love you.

429
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:15,267
Sorry, Mom. I have a lot
on my mind.

430
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,100
Next time, you don't have
to bring this here.

431
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:20,200
I can handle myself.
I can get my own lunch.

432
00:23:31,333 --> 00:23:33,667
Did they put your mom in jail
even though she's innocent?

433
00:23:35,300 --> 00:23:37,033
What's the case against her?

434
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:40,500
And who put her in jail?

435
00:23:53,467 --> 00:23:56,233
We have nothing left
to talk about.

436
00:23:56,333 --> 00:23:58,333
Didn't I tell you this is
the last time you'll see me?

437
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,367
It's over.

438
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:02,933
Why? Are you breaking up with me
just like that?

439
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,733
You'll just let go
all of a sudden?

440
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,033
You're giving up on us?

441
00:24:11,433 --> 00:24:15,133
Didn't we promise each other?
That no one will ever let go?

442
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,467
Red, we're not meant
for each other.

443
00:24:22,133 --> 00:24:24,633
So, stop talking to me.

444
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:27,167
We're over.

445
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:30,067
This is for our own good.

446
00:24:56,667 --> 00:24:58,333
I heard that Red was absent.

447
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,133
What?

448
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,433
See?

449
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:03,267
Red is the password
to get through to you.

450
00:25:03,367 --> 00:25:04,633
- Unbelievable.
- Sorry, Raichu.

451
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:06,367
I have a lot on my mind.

452
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:07,700
Are you sure that...

453
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:13,633
that Amanda had something to do
with my brother's death?

454
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:15,200
I admit.

455
00:25:15,267 --> 00:25:17,533
My investigation
had reached the point

456
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:21,533
where it says that Amanda
could be innocent.

457
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,567
Mom.

458
00:25:22,633 --> 00:25:23,467
Yeah?

459
00:25:23,533 --> 00:25:25,633
I have something important
to tell you.

460
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:27,533
What is it?

461
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:29,267
I will pay no matter
how much it costs!

462
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:31,300
Didn't we already have
that done before?

463
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:32,500
That's why the case
was expedited.

464
00:25:32,567 --> 00:25:34,700
Then do it again!

465
00:25:34,767 --> 00:25:36,333
So it's true?
